Breedon is a small village in Leicestershire, close to the Derby_ shire border. Its main feature is the church which stands on the hill high above the village. The village has its own Post Office,Nursery,General food store and a Newsagents. There are different social classes in the village,living in various types of houses.The A453 is a main road that runs through Breedon and then goes on to the City of Birmingham. The main Industrey in Breedon is quarrying at the two quarries,Breedon and Cloud Hill.Most of the rest of the land is used for farming.
